<section class="content-section">
  <h2>secure?</h2>
  <h3 class="section-description"><strong>Prompt injection</strong> isn't an <strong>LLM</strong> problem,<br> it's an <strong>infrastructure</strong> problem.</h3>

  <div class="container security-more">
    <p><strong>mlld</strong> tracks what data <em>is</em> and enforces where it can <em>go</em> at the runtime level. The LLM doesn't get a vote.</p>

    <p>No magic. No proprietary pixie dust. Just classic security principles applied to a new problem. mlld's primitives help you do the work of securing your stuff.</p>

    <p>From the cocreator of npm audit and Code4rena</p>
  </div>

</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>llm scripting?</h2>
  <h3 class="section-description">If you've experienced the <strong>pain</strong>,<br> you know what you <strong>need</strong> it to be.</h3>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Tired of repeating yourself</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          <p class="pain-quote">“I’d do a lot more with LLMs if constantly assembling and re-assembling context wasn’t such a chore.”</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Tired of wrong tools for the job</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          <p class="pain-quote">“I just want to script LLMs. Don’t give me a chat app or an uber-agent or a magic black box. Give me a unix pipe.”</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Tired of shipping without guardrails</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          <p class="pain-quote">“I can’t ship LLM workflows because I can’t secure them. Everyone handwaves ‘defense in depth’ and nobody has auditable tooling for it.”</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section">
  <h2>finally</h2>
  <h3 class="section-description">If you've seen the <strong>possibility</strong>,<br> you know what you <strong>want</strong> it to be.</h3>
  <hr>

  <h3 class="section-description">Auditable, defensible</h3>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-grid">

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Labels track identity, not content. No transformation strips them.</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['label-propagation'] or examples['label-propagation'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Label data. Sign instructions. Guards enforce the rules.</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['guard-mcp-tools'] or examples['guard-mcp-tools'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Classify once, enforce everywhere.</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['policy-config'] or examples['policy-config'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">Credentials never enter the variable namespace. Nothing to exfiltrate.</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['sealed-credentials'] or examples['sealed-credentials'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>

  <h3 class="section-description">Less code, more fun</h3>
  
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-grid">

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">
          Your pipeline crashed at call 73. mlld picks up at 74.
          <span>Resume or retry from a named checkpoint, a specific function call, or even the middle of a loop.</span>
        </h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['checkpoint-resume'] or examples['checkpoint-resume'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
          
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">{{ (examples.default['parallel-fanout'] or examples['parallel-fanout']).heading }}</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['parallel-fanout'] or examples['parallel-fanout'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-row">
        <span class="vertical-line"></span>
        <h3 class="card-heading">{{ (examples.default['anonymous-retry'] or examples['anonymous-retry']).heading }}</h3>
        <div class="card-content">
          {% set example = examples.default['anonymous-retry'] or examples['anonymous-retry'] %}
          {% include "components/mlld-example.njk" %}
        </div>
      </div>

